# Sudoku Solver Skeleton Implementation Plan

## Goal
Create a `SudokuSolver.java` file that acts as a scaffold for the user to implement the recursive backtracking algorithm. The file will contain all necessary boilerplate and helper methods.

## Proposed Changes

### `src/`
#### [NEW] [SudokuSolver.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/Soduko/src/SudokuSolver.java)
- **`main(String[] args)`**:
    - Initialize a sample 9x9 Sudoku grid (array of arrays).
    - Call `printBoard` to show initial state.
    - Call `solve` (the method the user will write).
    - Print the result.
- **`printBoard(int[][] board)`**:
    - loops through the board and prints it nicely to the console.
- **`isValid(int[][] board, int row, int col, int num)`**:
    - Checks if placing `num` at `board[row][col]` is valid according to Sudoku rules (row, column, and 3x3 subgrid).
- **`solve(int[][] board)`**:
    - **STUB ONLY**. This will return a boolean or void (likely boolean to indicate success) but will be empty/todo for the user.

## Verification
- Compile `SudokuSolver.java`.
- Run main to see the initial board printed and the stub called.
